<section id="faq">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sechead">
      <div class="eyebrow">Questions</div>
      <h2>Asked often, answered plainly.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
      <details>
        <summary>Is it really unlimited, or is there a hidden fair-usage policy?</summary>
        <p>Really unlimited. There is no usage cap, no throttling threshold, and no speed reduction at any point in the month. If we ever introduce a limit on any plan, we will say so on this page in the same size text as the price.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do you offer fibre or wireless?</summary>
        <p>Both. Where our fibre passes your street, we run a cable straight to your home or office. Where it doesn't yet, we beam the same unlimited service wirelessly from a nearby mast to a small rooftop radio — and both run on our own fibre backbone with multiple upstream carriers. You get the plan; we pick the best way to deliver it.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What does installation involve?</summary>
        <p>For fibre, we run a drop cable from the street to an indoor router. For wireless, a technician mounts a book-sized radio on your roof and cables it to your router. Either way we confirm your speeds before leaving — standard installation is free on home plans during launch.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do I pay?</summary>
        <p>Via M-Pesa paybill, monthly in advance. No contracts and no penalties — if you stop paying, service pauses; when you pay again, your home lights back up.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What speeds will I actually get?</summary>
        <p>The speed on your plan is the speed we provision to your connection, fibre or wireless. Wi-Fi speeds inside your house depend on your router placement and walls; our technicians position the router for the best real-world coverage during installation.</p>
